cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing video multicast over heterogeneous channels. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on maximizing the quality of experience (QoE) of a video multicast. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper proposes an application-layer forward error correction (AL-FEC) code rate allocation scheme. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a scheme to suppress QoE fluctuations for clients with marginal channel qualities. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper mentions the use of mixed spatial-temporal-amplitude scalability in the video coding, but this is not the main focus of the paper.
